HEADWORD: cytoskeleton
<hw>cy`to*skel"e*ton</hw> <pr>(s⟦imac⟧`t⟦osl⟧*sk⟦ecr⟧l"⟦icr⟧*t'n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Cell Biology)</fld> <def>An arrangement of
microtubules, microfilaments, and larger filaments within a cell serving
to provide structural support of components of the cell, and to
transport components from one part of the cell to another; the filaments
are composed of protein and form a latticelike arrangement which may
change rapidly with time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

